id: pm-lold
title: MCP ping method not handled — returns 'Unsupported MCP method' instead of empty response
description: "MCP protocol 2025-06-18 spec defines a `ping` method that should return an empty result `{}`. The pm-mcp server's handleRequest() falls through to `throw new PmCliError('Unsupported MCP method: ping', 64)` which writes a JSON-RPC error frame. Clients (e.g. Claude Code) that send ping for keep-alive get an error instead of a no-op. Evidence: server.ts line 1195 is the final throw; no case for 'ping' exists."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
